        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong></strong><b>Pro bono Work to Empower and Represent Act of 2022 or the POWER 2.0 Act</b></p> <p>This bill makes permanent the requirement for the chief judge of each federal judicial district to lead, at least annually, a public event to promote pro bono legal services for survivors of domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault, and stalking. </p> <p>The requirement was enacted in 2018; it is scheduled to sunset after a four-year period.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
